---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Preventing Returns: How Retailers Can Tackle Bracketing and Fit Issues - parcelLab"
  description="Learn how retailers can reduce bracketing returns through AI-powered sizing, personalized returns experiences, and balanced return policies."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Returns</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">Preventing Returns: How Retailers Can Tackle Bracketing and Fit Issues</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Dag Erlandsson</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2024-10-28">October 28, 2024</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>6 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Bracketing occurs when consumers order multiple sizes or versions of a product for trial purposes, then return unwanted items. This behavior is most prevalent in apparel and footwear, particularly among first-time customers -- and it's costing retailers billions.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">The Problem at Scale</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-medium text-[var(--ink)]">Returns cost retailers approximately $743 billion annually, with 67% of online shoppers classified as serial returners.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">What Is Bracketing and How Does It Affect Retailers?</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Research indicates that 75% of consumers say that sizes are inconsistent between brands. Additionally, a Bold Metrics survey found that 94% of customers consider figuring out their size online to be frustrating. Rather than measuring themselves, most shoppers prefer ordering various sizes and returning poor fits.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Proactive Sizing Guidance to Prevent Returns</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          AI-powered solutions address the root cause -- size uncertainty. Bold Metrics' approach involves collecting measurements (age, height, weight) to create a digital profile that recommends optimal sizing and fit predictions. This methodology achieves an 88% completion rate for the digital twin information.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">How You Can Recover Revenue When Bracketing Happens</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Despite prevention efforts, some bracketing returns are inevitable. Retailers should implement personalized returns experiences to recover as much revenue as possible:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Exchange encouragement</strong> -- guide customers toward alternative sizes or products</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Store credit incentives</strong> -- e.g., $5 vouchers for credit selection over refunds</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Alternative product suggestions</strong> -- recommend items that may better suit the customer</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Targeted campaigns</strong> -- encourage additional purchases during the returns flow</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Balancing Charging for Returns and the Customer Experience</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Returns policies significantly influence purchasing decisions, especially for first-time buyers. Survey data revealed that only 28% of retailers currently charge for returns, while 20% are considering implementation.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Charging can deter bracketing behavior but risks customer satisfaction. A balanced approach involves nuanced rules: offering free returns to first-time customers and loyalty members while charging serial returners. This strategy reduces problematic returns while maintaining positive brand relationships.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">From Purchase to Return: Building Lasting Relationships</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Sustainable customer relationships require attention at every stage:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Pre-Purchase</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Provide accurate, simple sizing determination tools that help customers choose the right fit the first time around.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Post-Purchase</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Deliver personalized returns experiences that give customers control and options, turning potential frustrations into loyalty-building moments.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Even advanced sizing technology cannot eliminate all returns, making excellent returns management essential for minimizing revenue loss and building loyalty. The key is combining prevention with recovery strategies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
